  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "1KKwJA/hIQ0hKRsFGrHByBoj1Rw=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# epochs distribute revenue proportionally by weighted token supply\n\n## Objects Involved\n- **Source**: Epoch \u2014 a time period with iPOWA supply, cPOWA supply, and a weight factor\n- **Target**: DistributionRecord \u2014 a record of actual revenue distributed to an epoch's token contracts\n\n## Relationship\n\nEach epoch's share of total revenue is:\n```\nepochWeightedSupply = (iPOWA_supply + cPOWA_supply) \u00d7 weight\nepochShare = epochWeightedSupply / totalWeightedSupply \u00d7 totalRevenue\n```\n\nWithin an epoch, revenue splits further between iPOWA and cPOWA proportionally to their individual weighted supplies. A single revenue deposit creates one DistributionRecord per epoch.\n\nThe weight factor controls relative importance: weight=1.0 means full participation, weight=0.5 means half. This enables governance to phase epochs in/out gradually.\n\n## Implications\n\n- Adding a new epoch dilutes all existing epochs' revenue share (totalWeightedSupply increases)\n- Changing an epoch's weight recalculates all epoch shares (zero-sum redistribution)\n- Distribution records are immutable once created \u2014 they represent on-chain facts\n- Dust (1-2 wei rounding error per epoch) is inherent to the proportional math and must be tracked explicitly\n\n---\n\nRelevant Notes:\n- [[powa-revenue-distribution model captures epoch-based token revenue sharing]]\n- [[masterchef accumulator pattern enables per-token revenue tracking]]\n\nTopics:\n- [[object relations]]\n- [[schema design]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z"
    }
  },
